<!-- Do not remove this test for UTF-8: if “Ω” doesn’t appear as greek uppercase omega letter enclosed in quotation marks, you should use an editor that supports UTF-8, not this one. -->
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>go-core</id>
    <version>2.2.2</version>
    <packageSourceUrl>https://github.com/core-coin/gocore-chocolatey</packageSourceUrl>
    <title>go-core (Install)</title>
    <projectUrl>https://coreblockchain.cc/</projectUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/core-coin/go-core/blob/master/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>true</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <authors>core</authors>
    <owners>core</owners>
    <summary>Official Go implementation of the CORE blockchain protocol (gocore CLI).</summary>
    <description>Official Golang implementation of the CORE protocol.</description>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/core-coin/go-core</projectSourceUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://github.com/core-coin/go-core/blob/master/README.md</docsUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/core-coin/go-core/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <tags>Core-coin Go-core Blockchain Crypto</tags>
    <releaseNotes>
v2.2.2 — full upgrade from the previous chocolatey release (1.1.4, May 2022). Covers the entire v2.x line. Per-version detail: https://github.com/core-coin/go-core/releases

Highlights since 1.1.4:
- Major version 2.0: protocol upgrade (Gocore v2, #441).
- Trusted checkpoints added for Mainnet and Devin (#449, #463).
- Smart contract API extensions (#481); `balanceOf` now accepts a feature parameter (#484).
- JWT authentication support for RPC (#472).
- RandomY VM updated to a RandomX 1.2.1 baseline (#477).
- Fix: ed448 signature verification corner case (via go-goldilocks v1.0.16, #470).
- Fix: graphql address parsing (#475).
- Fix: devp2p stability (#473, #474).
- Built with Go 1.21.
    </releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="mingw" version="11.2.0.07112021" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
